Include quadratic features for each continuous input with the interaction of the categorical and the linear features.

Fit the sklearn logistic regression model consistent with fit_01. By default, sklearn's logistic regression method uses a penalized or regularized model. It does not just minimize the loss or maximize the likelihood. To force sklearn to match statsmodels we must set the penalty = 'none'.

In [17]:
sk_01_mle = LogisticRegression(penalty='none', solver='lbfgs', max_iter=5001, fit_intercept=True).fit(X_01, y_01.ravel())

def extract_sklearn_coefs(sk_mod):
    return list(sk_mod.intercept_.ravel()) + list(sk_mod.coef_.ravel())

Which model will do the best on new data? We will approximate new data by splitting the existing data set into training and testing splits.

Resample the data¶

Use an existing method from sklearn to manage the data splitting.

We will start with K-fold cross-validation.

In [57]:
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold
In [58]:
kf05 = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=101)
In [60]:
kf05
Out[60]:
KFold(n_splits=5, random_state=101, shuffle=True)

Create objects to help us visualize the behavior of cross-validation.

In [61]:
train_list = []
test_list = []

    train_list.append( df.iloc[ train_id, :].copy() )
    test_list.append( df.iloc[ test_id, :].copy() )

Execute cross validation¶

Define a function which fits on the training set and assess on the test set - but for lecture also assess on the training set so we can compare with the test set performance.

In [82]:
def evaluate_model_with_cv(cv, my_data, my_formula, my_mod):
    y, X = dmatrices(my_formula, data = my_data)
    
    train_res = []
    test_res = []
    
    for train_id, test_id in cv.split(X):
        X_train, X_test = X[train_id], X[test_id]
        y_train, y_test = y[train_id], y[test_id]
        
        mod_fit = my_mod.fit(X_train, y_train.ravel())
        
        train_res.append( mod_fit.score(X_train, y_train.ravel()) )
        test_res.append( mod_fit.score(X_test, y_test.ravel()) )
    
    train_df = pd.DataFrame({'Accuracy': train_res})
    train_df['from_set'] = 'training'
    train_df['fold_id'] = train_df.index + 1
    
    test_df = pd.DataFrame({'Accuracy': test_res})
    test_df['from_set'] = 'testing'
    test_df['fold_id'] = test_df.index + 1
    
    return pd.concat([train_df, test_df]).reset_index(drop=True)

Regularization¶

Ridge Penalty or L2-norm¶

$$Loss + Penalty = C \sum_{n=1}^{N} \bigg(-y_n \log\left(Probability_n\right) - \left(1 - y_n\right) \log\left(1 - Probability_n\right) \bigg) + \frac{1}{2} \sum_{d=0}^{D} \left( \beta_{d}^{2}\right)$$
